'''Darian Lane''' is an American film writer, director and producer. Lane is best known as an Assistant Director and Producer of Music Videos and Commercials. Most notable for ''Muhammad Ali, Black-Eyed Peas, Chris Brown, Beyoncé, Ashlee Simpson, 50 Cent, Pharrell & Gwen Stefani, Natalie Portman, Proactive, Windsor Pilates, Pepsi, American Express and Pet Smart''.
Darian Lane was born in Philadelphia, PA, raised in Bethesda, MD. Both of his parents are attorneys. Darian Lane had ambitions of becoming a lawyer until he discovered film. Once he graduated Arizona State University, he moved to Los Angeles to study at the Sanford Meisner Theatre. There he wrote and directed two produced plays entitled, ''Beautiful Corpses'' and ''The Broadway Play'' for the Jewel Box Center Theatre, American Renegade Theatre and Stella Adler Theatre.
To supplement his income, Lane began working as a Production Assistant on Music Videos and Commercials and before long he moved up to Assistant Director and Producer. Though he preferred playwrighting, Lane merged into writing for film. His first film ''The Hitchhiking Game'' based on a Milan Kundera short story went to Cannes in 2008. He followed it up with his law school drama ''casebook'' and later ''The Collector'', which went to LA/NY and Malibu Film Festivals.
Since then Lane has written two published novels, ''The Girlfriend Experience & Flashy Fiction (The Los Angeles Edition)''.
He currently resides in Malibu, California.

‘’’Dubai World Central Commercial City’’’ is the district that acts as the center of activities in the rest of [[Dubai World Central]]. There will be more than 850 towers ranging from 1-45 storeys tall, along with 25 hotels ranging from 3 to 5 star and other amenities.<ref name=BNC>{{cite web|title=Commercial City - Dubai World Central|url=https://www.bncnetwork.net/Project/Commercial_City_-_Dubai_World_Central/KMd9rG9bnc4ck=|publisher=BNC network|accessdate=4 November 2013}}</ref> The urban will include 1400 ha site and be the workplace for an estimated 225,000 people.<ref name=Logistics>{{cite web|title=Dubai Logistics City Planning Regulations.& Development Guidelines.|url=http://www.dwc.ae/application-forms/DWC_LogisiticsDistrict_PlanningRegulation&DevelopmentGuidelines_012009.pdf|accessdate=4 November 2013}}</ref>
==Zones== Dubai World Central Commercial City is further split into eight zones. {{Infobox person |name = Prof. Rabbi Ahron Daum |image = |caption = |birth_name = Ahron Daum |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1959|1|6}} |birth_place = {{nowrap|[[Bnei Brak]], [[Israel]]}} |death_date = |death_place = |years_active = 1982–present |occupation = Rabbi, professor, author, educator |spouse = Francine |children = 3 |alma_mater = |religion = [[Orthodox Judaism]]
|website = {{url|http://www.bestjewishstudies.com/}} }} '''Ahron Daum''' (born January 6 1951) is an Israeli-born [[Modern Orthodox Judaism|Modern-Orthodox]] [[rabbi]], educator, author, and former [[chief rabbi]] of [[Frankfurt am Main]], currently residing in [[Antwerp, Belgium]]. ==Personal life and education== Ahron Daum was born on the 6th of January 1951 in [[Bnei Brak, Israel]]. He was born into a religious [[Ashkenazi]] family. His father Schmuel Daum was an important educator, writer, and communal figure, hailing from a prominent rabbinic family from Poland and Bohemia. His mother Rivka Gina Daum hailed from a prosperous trader family in Sopron, Hungary. He has three younger brothers. His intensive religious training began at age 13 in the famous Lithuanian-Chassidic “Ruzhin” Yeshiva in [[Bnei Brak]]. At age 14, he left for the UK where he continued his studies at the Yeshiva Ha-Rama and later on moved to the well-known Zionistic Yeshiva Etz Chaim in [[Montreux, Switzerland]]. In 1975, after obtaining his Baccalaureate Degree in Switzerland, he went to [[Jews' College|Jews’ College]], [[University of London]], where he obtained a Bachelor’s Degree in Jewish Studies (with Honours){{cite web |title=Levine, Frank (1977) |url=http://www.bestjewishstudies.com/Diplomas-and-certificates |publisher=Rabbi Daum official website}}. From 1978 he attended the [[Rabbi Isaac Elchanan Theological Seminary]] (RIETS '82) of [[Yeshiva University]], [[New York]] where he obtained a Master’s Degree in Biblical Studies (with Honours){{cite web |title=Charlop, Rabbi Zevulun (1982) |url=http://www.bestjewishstudies.com/Diplomas-and-certificates |publisher=Rabbi Daum official website}} and his rabbinical ordination personally signed and handed by Prof. Rabbi [[Joseph Soloveitchik]]. Declining the offer to continue his studies in order to obtain the title of [[Dayan]], he returned to Europe where he married Francine Frenkel with whom he has three daughters. He speaks Hebrew, English, German, French, Dutch and Yiddish and has a passive knowledge of Aramaic and Latin. ==Rabbinical career== In 1982 he started his rabbinical career in Switzerland as a community Rabbi in the town of [[Biel]], a bilingual French/German town{{cite web |title=Gefter, J. (1985) |url=http://www.bestjewishstudies.com/Diplomas-and-certificates |publisher=Rabbi Daum official website}}. He left this post in 1986 to become a doctoral fellow at the Christlich-Jüdische Institut in [[Lucerne]], affiliated with the Theological Faculty of the [[University of Lucerne]], Switzerland. In 1987 he accepted the post of [[Chief Rabbi]] of the Jewish Community of [[Frankfurt am Main]]{{cite web |title=Sjazak, S. (1993) |url=http://www.bestjewishstudies.com/Diplomas-and-certificates |publisher=Rabbi Daum official website}}{{cite web |title=Schmidt, Martin (1992) |url=http://www.bestjewishstudies.com/sites/all/P1/letters%20of%20accomodation%20and%20aprobation%20in%20Hebrew%20and%20Euroepan%20Languages%20for%20my%20Halachic%20work%27Halacha%20Actuell%27.pdf |publisher=Rabbi Daum official website}}, Germany, at that time the largest and most prestigious Jewish Community of [[West Germany]]. In 1994, for family reasons, he resigned from his post as Chief Rabbi and moved to [[Antwerp, Belgium]], where the largest part of his family already lived. There he started to teach Judaism within the state school system and in Jewish day schools. In 1995 he accepted a position as lecturer in Jewish Law at the [[Faculty for Comparative Religion]] in [[Wilrijk]] (Antwerp) ,Belgium{{cite web |title=Vonck Ph.D., Prof. J.G. (1996) |url=http://www.bestjewishstudies.com/Diplomas-and-certificates |publisher=Rabbi Daum official website}}. In recognition of his teaching there and his works on [[Halacha]] the Faculty awarded him a Professorship Honoris Causa in Jewish Law. Since 2001 he also started, along with his wife, a series of outreach projects for [[Baal teshuva|Baalei Tshuva]] , non-Jews interested in Jewish studies and prospective converts to Judaism. Today this takes up most of his time and efforts and as part of these outreach activities he regularly organizes, in cooperation with the Netherlands-based Shalom Centre, study days on various topics within the field of Jewish studies. ==Work and publications== Prof. Rabbi Ahron Daum is a prolific author who has written on a diverse scope of topics within the field of Jewish studies. Whilst living in Switzerland he was a regular contributor of Halachic articles to the Jewish Swiss-German weekly "Jüdische Rundschau"{{cite web |title=Bollag, Peter (1991) |url=http://www.bestjewishstudies.com/sites/all/P1/letters%20of%20accomodation%20and%20aprobation%20in%20Hebrew%20and%20Euroepan%20Languages%20for%20my%20Halachic%20work%27Halacha%20Actuell%27.pdf |publisher=Rabbi Daum official website}}. During his tenure as [[Chief Rabbi]] of [[Frankfurt am Main]], he regularly wrote articles for "Die Jüdische Allgemeine" and the bi-monthly magazine "Die Gemeinde". Since 2010 he writes a monthly column for the magazine [[Joods Actueel]], the most widely circulated Jewish publication in Belgium. In these columns he covers the whole spectrum of Jewish Studies, for example his well-liked series on the history of Judaism since the [[Enlightenment in Western secular tradition|Enlightenment]]. He is the author of two books. His first book "Halacha aktuell"{{cite web |title=Jakobovits, Chief Rabbi (1991) |url=http://www.bestjewishstudies.com/sites/all/P1/letters%20of%20accomodation%20and%20aprobation%20in%20Hebrew%20and%20Euroepan%20Languages%20for%20my%20Halachic%20work%27Halacha%20Actuell%27.pdf |publisher=Rabbi Daum official website}}{{cite web |title=Diamant, Adolf (1992) |url=http://www.bestjewishstudies.com/sites/all/P1/letters%20of%20accomodation%20and%20aprobation%20in%20Hebrew%20and%20Euroepan%20Languages%20for%20my%20Halachic%20work%27Halacha%20Actuell%27.pdf |publisher=Rabbi Daum official website}}{{cite web |title=Ahren, Yizhak (1993) |url=http://www.bestjewishstudies.com/sites/all/P1/letters%20of%20accomodation%20and%20aprobation%20in%20Hebrew%20and%20Euroepan%20Languages%20for%20my%20Halachic%20work%27Halacha%20Actuell%27.pdf|publisher=Rabbi Daum official website}}{{cite web |title=Avraham Cahana Shapiro, Chief Rabbi of Israel (1991) |url=http://www.bestjewishstudies.com/sites/all/P1/letters%20of%20accomodation%20and%20aprobation%20in%20Hebrew%20and%20Euroepan%20Languages%20for%20my%20Halachic%20work%27Halacha%20Actuell%27.pdf |publisher=Rabbi Daum official website}}is a two-volume work, written in German, which treats [[Halacha|Halachic]] problems and issues of current interest as they appear in the Halachic literature and more specifically the [[Responsa]]. This work is unique in that it was the first book written in German during the post-war period that comprehensively deals with Halachic issues in the Responsa literature. It was therefore welcomed with great enthusiasm in the Halachic world and received approbations from many distinguished Halachic authorities. Certain articles from this book were written in Rabbinic Hebrew and were later separately published under the title "Iyunim b’Halacha". His second book was "Die Jüdische Feiertage in Sicht der Tradition" (The Jewish Festivals in View of he Tradition). It is a two-volume anthology combining Halachic articles, sermons, liturgical remarks, [[homiletic]] thoughts and folkloric and humorous tales connected to the [[Jewish holidays]] and [[Shabbat]]. He is presently working on a number of books in Dutch covering such diverse topics as [[Kabbalah]], [[Jewish History]], the contemporary Jewish World and its different affiliations and other issues. ==Published works== '''Books''' *''Halacha aktuell, Jüdische Religionsgestze und Bräuche im modernen Alltag'' (Haag und Herchen Verlag, Frankfurt am Main, 1992, 2 Vol., p. 387 – p. 773) *''Iyunim b’Halacha'' (Haag und Herchen Verlag, Frankfurt am Main, 1992, p. 93) *''Die Feiertage Israels, Die jüdischen Feiertage in er Sicht der Tradition'' (Herchen Verlag, Frankfurt am Main, vol. I, 1993, p.556, vol. II, 1994, p.557) *''"Das aschkenasische Rabbinat : Studien über Glaube und Schicksal"'' (Julius Carlebach) / ''Die Rolle des Rabbiners in Deutschland heute'' (Ahron Daum) ==References== {{reflist|2}} ==External links== * {{Official website|http://www.bestjewishstudies.com}} * [http://www.bestjewishstudies.com/Diplomas-and-certificates Diploma's and certificates] * [http://www.amazon.de/s/ref=ntt_athr_dp_sr_1?_encoding=UTF8&field-author=Ahron%20Daum Works by Ahron Daum] on Amazon

'''''Dr. Mak Yuree Vajramuni'''''
'''Born''' 30 July 1964 (age 49) Dhaka, Bangladesh.
'''Nationality''' Bangladeshi
'''Occupation''' Founder of Butthan Martial Arts
'''Dr. Yuree''' (born 30 April 1964) is a Bangladeshi born Grandmaster and Founder of Butthan: Art of stopping-fight and enlightenment. He has set the first world record in Martial Arts category amongst the eight SAARC countries. Dr. Yuree is a ten (10th) degree Black Belt & Professor in Martial science. Dr. Mak Yuree Known as Vajra Muni or Thunder Sage is scientifically proven World’s number one icon in psychophysical training and leading exponent in field of Meditation, Mind reconstruction and personal development. He is the World Record Holder for highest neuro-engagement ability in the World as concluded by the experiment in laboratory condition by the Discovery Channel team of scientists. Dr.Yuree is a Hall of Famer, selected as & featured as one of the top five SUPERHUMAN of the World by Discovery Channel. After the Scientific research & laboratory tests Vajra Muni is considered to be the most outstanding man with the ability to engage highest percentage (96%) of muscles of the body through commanding brain.
==Cadet life==
Dr. Yuree grew up in the Iron discipline of the Military boarding school and showed outstanding qualities from the early age. After finishing primary education his life as a young boy and Cadet began in the Military feeder institution developed under the British Military official standard and headed by British Sr. Military personnel. A remarkably talented cadet with dynamic excellence, he always took the lead in his studies like Military science, Physical training, Obstacle course, Unarmed combat, Military drills. He was specially selected to carry the National flag in the pilot unit 'Color Party' as an exemplary performer and later was honored with the award “Distinguished Cadet” by the alumni association.
During his vacations he used to train under distinguished Masters of different disciplines like Yoga, Lathi Khela (pole fighting), Bando (Burmese self-defense system) etc.
==World Records==
After twenty years of rigorous training Dr. Yuree Vajra Muni’s first world record was set at National Exhibition Center (NEC), Birmingham, England. In 2010 Grandmaster Yuree Vajra Muni at an international Martial Arts show he broke two baseball bats in a bundle with a single shin-kick. Tom Hibbert, MBE (Medal of British Empire), President of World All Style Kickboxing Federation, UK and Paul Clifton, editor Combat Magazine, who were present at the show personally congratulated Dr. Yuree on his world record.
At the King’s Battlegound show at Nottingham, UK, Yuree set his second world record by breaking three baseball bats placed in AEP (alternative end placement) formation in 5.3 seconds and till today no one has attempted to challenge this record. In 2012 for this third world record Dr. Yuree broke three baseball bats in regular formation in a single kick at NEC, Birmingham, UK. http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YYJAXnlczGc His fourth world record, occurred during the filming of the SUPERHUMAN showdown by Discovery Channel, Dr. Yuree was subjected to the scientific experiments and laboratory tests which proved that he has the ability to recruit the highest percentage (96%) of muscles of the body through brain command. http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7hVrzRZ6H1k
==Philosophy==
Grandmaster Dr. Yuree advocates and practices ‘TAN-PA’ philosophy. It is a Burmese term, ‘TAN’ means iron and ‘PA’ means flower. Together, the term combines hard and soft methods. There are two logical aspects of ‘TANPA’, the Fighting Art Training and the Corporeal Training. Technically feasible optimum result could be attainable by combining seemingly reverse methods. The varying requirement of speed, harshness, firmness, stability, laxity of timing, etc. justify suitability of the method. According to Dr. Yure’s ‘TANPA’ philosophy, human body, mind and spirit work in unison. The hard method depends on body while the soft method depends on practice and exercise. This philosophy judges everything from practical point of view and takes impartial steps, an important feature of BUTTHAN. So, ‘TANPA’ philosophy implies hard hitting yet soft tackling method. Dr. Yuree’s most inspiring philosophical quotation is “Everything is possible if we try enough”.
==Research and Development==
As a young practitioner who started his training at the age of 9 years old with Burmese classical art Bando. In later stages Dr. Yuree also trained in characters and applications of different martial art systems. During his trainings, two things stroked Dr. Yuree, the level of effectiveness of these techniques and the utility and reflection of learning these arts to personal development. He felt that the practical applications of these arts were limited to a certain degree in both the sphere of real life street fight scenario and also in contributing to the development of a well-rounded personality. In search of an answer, he started a research and development on different martial arts systems, visiting almost 50 different countries, experiencing 40 different martial arts systems. He also emphasized studying the history of martial arts in the world. He is credited for the research over the decades to revive the historical linkage of Kanchipuram India and Shaolin temple, China – a contribution to global Martial Art development.
==Founding Butthan==
As Dr. Yuree went through his R&D on different self-defense systems and military combative his attention was taken to one thing besides the two earlier mentioned focus points of his research– the south Asian lost heritage of martial arts. Vajra Muni considered the Art of Self-defense as a major instrument in restructuring and empowering human life. He started working to develop a comprehensive self-defense system from South Asian heritage point of view which would effectively contribute in personal development in the context of modern day life.
The term “Butthan” came into official use first in 1991 and in 1998 World Butthan Federation was registered in Texas, Houston. In 2009 the name was changed to International Butthan Federation. In March 2013, National Sports Council of Bangladesh officially recognized Butthan as a sport.
The followers, students, instructors and patrons of Butthan are continuing their mission to promote Butthan in four corners of the world.
==Security, Law Enforcement and Military training==
Dr. Yuree is Director General of “Global Executive Protection & Security Training Agency” and Commandant of “Rangers Academy of Security & Defense”. Grandmaster Prof. Dr. Yuree is a former UN Representative & Goodwill Ambassador to World Human Rights Service Council. Dr.Yuree is a graduate from National Security Academy, USA and completed the highest degree (SIA level-3) under UK home office. He is a certified Fire Marshal, a security management expert, law-enforcement & Master defensive tactics specialist, trainer & consultant to different Military, Security & Intelligence agencies at home and abroad. He specializes in CQB (close quarter battle) and close protection (body guarding). Apart from this he is also certified in High-rise building security, airport security, bank security, first-aid at work, tactical driving, aviation security, explosive search and recognition etc. He is enjoying his international reputation in this field for the last 23 years. He is also the inventor of “MY” security baton, being used by different law enforcement and private security agencies including UN Peace keeping force.
Dr. Yuree introduced “Combat Self-Defense” (CSD) System, which is a real life self-defense solution for civilians and specially appreciated by the Law Enforcement and close protection operatives.
Dr. Yuree is a member of American Society of Law Enforcement Trainers (ASLET), USA, International Law Enforcement Training Agency, UK, American Society for Industrial Security (ASIS), USA and International Police Tactics Instructors Association, USA.
==Lathi Khela – the folk heritage==
Lathi Khela is a Bangladeshi folk heritage and a dying art. Dr. Yuree trained and collected materials from the different lineage practicing various forms of Lathi Khela. He was fortunate enough to receive close door lessons from the Late Ostad Sirajul Haque Chowhdury who nationally reorganized the Art of Lathi Khela after partition (1947). Dr. Yuree won a gold medal in a traditional Lathi Khela competition. Bangladesh Lathail Bahini also awarded him with the title “Ostad E Azam” (the Great amongst the Masters). Dr. Yuree by preserving this sport is now formally presenting Lathi Khela in front of national and international critics and scholars. In 2013, National Museum Bangladesh brought out a commemorative volume celebrating its 100 years. The publication contained papers written by the most illustrious scholars and researchers of Bangladesh and contained a research paper by Dr. Yuree titled “Lathi Khela – the National Heritage”. The paper was appreciated and read out later in an international seminar. http://www.lathikhela.com/
==Butthan Meditation===
Superhuman Mind System is a science based instruction to help practitioners to transform their life by achieving clarity of thought and energizing the body mind connection to unlock hidden potentials. It is a non-religious, secular, mind training system derived from scientific principles in the light of ancient South-Asian heritage. http://butthanmeditation.org/
==Becoming the Superhuman==
In 2012, the Discovery Channel invited Dr. Yuree Vajramuni to join the “Superhuman” showdown selection process worldwide. In the process of semi-final and final selection, he was chosen as the strongest shin-kicker of the planet, considering his outstanding psychophysical ability and shin-kick prowess. During the selection he was subjected to extensive medical test and laboratory experiments, in which he demonstrated the highest recorded psychophysical engagement. Most people have a lack of neuron power which means that their brains are unable to trigger the full extent of muscle power at their disposal. This was measured by Dr. Emma Rose, who specializes on such tests with the help of a Dynamometer to measure muscle force, Transcranial Magnetic stimulator which tells the brain to engage all muscles, connected with a monitor to display the strength in a graphical output. Once the magnetic stimulator was placed on top of the head, Dr. Yuree was asked to get ready, at which point he started focusing on Butthan Meditation and at that stage the Magnetic stimulator sent an electric impulse through his body while Vajramuni engaged his leg connected with the Dynamometer in action. Once the impulse was sent, the monitor displayed that Vajramuni was able to engage 96% of his quadriceps muscles fibers were recruited on command from his brain. The power of the mind control is being displayed in his unique ability to recruit the maximum amount of muscle power on command. This was surprising to the Scientists who conducted the experiment and far exceeded their expectation.
Dr. Yure was selected and featured on Discovery Channel as one of the top five Superhuman of the world in Strength category. In May 2012, Discovery Channel filmed Grandmaster Dr. Yuree’s Superhuman abilities and the demonstration of strongest shin-kick of this planet in Riverside Studio, London. The documentary has earned enormous appreciation and accolades all over the world. The show has been dubbed in many different languages and is currently being telecast in Europe by Quest Channel.
American Scientist Prof. Greg White said, “What we saw with MAK Yuree is that he can actually recruit virtually all of his muscles. Strength or power production is about not only the size of the muscle itself, bigger muscle, more power. It’s actually about the amount of muscle we can recruit consciously with our brain.” Discovery Channel’s message was “MAK Yuree’s massive leg power is incredible. “
==Honors & Awards==
Dr. Yuree is the recipient of many national and international awards of which the following are mentionable:
• Selected & Featured as one of the top Five SUPERHUMAN of the World by DISCOVERY Channel. • World Record Re-set -2012 (at Martial Arts Show, NEC, Birmingham, UK) • Most Outstanding Achievers Award Trophy, 2011, Martial Arts Show, NEC, UK. • World Record Accomplished -2010 (at Martial Arts Show, NEC, Birmingham, UK) • Grand Master Pinnacle Award – 2009 (World Head of Families Sokeship Council ,USA • Grand Master of the Year – 2009. (London Martial Arts Hall of Fame, UK) • Grand Master of the Year – 2008. (World Black Belt Martial Arts Hall of Fame, Malaysia • Grand Master of the Year – 2007. (Universal Martial Arts Hall of Fame, USA) • Peaceful Dragon Golden Claws – Title award by Diplomatic Mission, Embassy of Royal Bhutan. • Grand Master of the Year – 2007. (World Martial Arts Hall of Fame, USA) • World Leader in Combat Martial Arts . (Int’l Combat Martial Arts Unions Hall of Fame,2006) • Title Award “Vajra Muni” from School of Varma kalai & Siddah,India. • Thant Sin Pan and Ambassador (Myanmar Martial Art Federation - 2005) • Official Successor of Grand Master Khin Maung Gyi (President- South East Asia Bando Assoc:,1991) • Distinguished Cadet Award – 1987 (JEXCA-Military Feeder Institution Alumni)

(2013) }} '''''Baadshah''''' is the feature film soundtrack of the 2013 Telugu film ''[[Baadshah (2013 film)|Baadshah]]'' starring [[N. T. Rama Rao Jr.|Jr. NTR]] & [[Kajal Aggarwal]] in the lead roles directed by [[Srinu Vaitla]]. The soundtrack consists of 6 Tracks all composed by [[S. Thaman]] with [[Ramajogayya Sastry]] penning 3 of them and [[Krishna Chaitanya (lyricist)|Krishna Chaitanya]], Viswa, Bhaskarabhatla Ravikumar penning each.{{cite web|url=http://www.teluguone.com/tmdb/news/Baadshah-Audio-and-Track-List-Poster-en-21593c1.html|title=Baadshah Audio and Track List Poster|publisher=TeluguOne|accessdate=March 14, 2013}} The Soundtrack Album was released by [[Aditya Music]]{{cite web|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/audio-rights-of-telugu-film-baadshah-acquired-by--aditya-music/376914-71-216.html|title=Audio rights of Telugu film 'Baadshah' acquired by Aditya music|publisher=IBN Live|accessdate=March 6, 2013 11:25 AM IST}} on March 17, 2013 which co-incided with a heavy yet catastrophic promotional event held at [[Ramanaidu Studios]] which is located at [[Nanakramguda]] of [[Hyderabad, India|Hyderabad]] on the same day.{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/130318/news-current-affairs/article/fan-crushed-death-audio-release-jr-ntrs-baadshah|title=Fan crushed to death at audio release of Jr NTR's Baadshah|publisher=Deccan Chronicle|accessdate=March 18, 2013}} The audio received positive response from the critics as well as audience.{{cite web|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-03-19/news-interviews/37842709_1_baadshah-ss-thaman-response|title=Thaman elated with audio response|publisher=The Times of India|accessdate=March 19, 2013 03:14 PM IST}} == Production == [[S. Thaman]] was roped in as the Music Director of the film which marks his second collaboration with [[N. T. Rama Rao Jr.|Jr. NTR]] after ''[[Brindavanam (film)|Brindavanam]]'' and with [[Srinu Vaitla]] after ''[[Dookudu]]''. In April 2012, Thaman started composing music for the film and he first completed the title track of the film.{{cite web|url=http://www.chitramala.in/news/thaman-completes-badshah-title-song-128714.html|title=Thaman completes Badshah title song!|publisher=chitramala.com |accessdate=April 17, 2012 05:53 PM IST}} Music Sitting Discussions were held at Ooty in May 2012.{{cite web|url=http://www.supergoodmovies.com/44226/tollywood/jr-ntr-s-badshah-music-sittings-in-ooty-news-details |title=Jr NTR's 'Badshah' Music Sittings in Ooty |publisher=supergoodmovies.com |accessdate=May 7, 2012}} By June 2012, Thaman reported that he completed 3 songs and is working hard early mornings for fast & better results.{{cite web|url=http://www.teluguone.com/tmdb/news/Thaman-Early-Morning-Efforts-For-NTR-en-14636c1.html|title=Thaman Early Morning Efforts For NTR|publisher=TeluguOne|accessdate=June 6, 2012}} In the same month, reports emerged that the film's lead actress [[Kajal Aggarwal]] would make her debut as a Playback singer by singing a song in this film as per Thaman's request.{{cite web|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-06-23/news-interviews/32381197_1_kajal-agarwal-image-makeover-tinsel-town|title=Will Kajal sing for Baadshah?|publisher=The Times of India|accessdate=June 23, 2012 01:53 PM IST}} In July 2012, Popular R&B singer [[Akon]] was said to be roped in to sing a song in this film.{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/article/83924.html|title=Akon for NTR's Baadshah is official|publisher=IndiaGlitz|accessdate=July 19, 2012}} Added to this, speculations arised that Akon and Kajal would croon together for a peppy song in the album.{{cite web|url=http://www.ycinemas.in/2012/06/kajal-to-sing-along-with-akon-for-ntrs.html|title=Kajal Agarwal to sing along with Akon for NTR's Baadshah|publisher=ycinemas.com|accessdate=June 24, 2012 07:50 PM IST}} However Kajal dismissed the rumors that she was going to sing in this or any other film further adding that he was totally baffled after hearing this news.{{cite web|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-06-29/news-interviews/32458426_1_kajal-aggarwal-naan-mahan-alla-film|title=Kajal Aggarwal is not singing|publisher=The Times of India|accessdate=June 29, 2012 12:00 AM IST}} The makers dropped the idea of roping in Akon due to his non-availability due to busy schedules and remuneration which neared 3 Crores.{{cite web|url=http://www.myfirstshow.com/news/view/13192/Akon-not-singing-for-NTR.html|title=Akon not singing for NTR|publisher=myfirstshow.com|accessdate=}} In August 2012, Thaman went to Bangkok to record the Theme song of the film. He joined hands with the famous Bangkok philharmonic orchestra. Singers [[Rahul Nambiar]], [[Ranjith (singer)|Ranjith]], [[Suchitra]], who accompanied him to Bangkok provided the additional vocals and all of them returned back to Chennai later.{{cite web|url=http://idlebrain.com/news/2000march20/thaman-baadshahtheme.html|title=Thaman completes theme song for Baadshah|publisher=idlebrain.com|accessdate=August 13, 2012}} In September 2012, the scratch version of the song "Sairo Sairo" was leaked into the Internet. The song received enormously positive response almost turning a chartbuster with many praising Thaman's work as different from his old tunes.{{cite web|url=http://www.teluguone.com/tmdb/news/NTR-Baadshah-Leaked-Song-Rocking--17569c1.html|title=NTR Baadshah Leaked Song Rocking|publisher=TeluguOne|accessdate=Sep 22, 2012}} In February 2013, It was revealed that Tamil Hero [[Silambarasan|Simbu]] crooned the song "Diamond Girl", which marks his first song in Telugu.{{cite web|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-02-25/news-interviews/37288200_1_vaalu-vettai-mannan-simbu|title=Simbu croons for NTR Junior in 'Baadshah'|publisher=The Times of India|accessdate=Feb 25, 2013 09:57 AM IST}} Along with this, another song was crooned by [[Daler Mehndi]]. Co-incidentally, both songs were penned by [[Ramajogayya Sastry]].{{cite web|url=http://telugu.way2movies.com/newssingle_telugu/Daler-Mehndi-croons-for-NTR%E2%80%99s-Baadshah--4-301828.html|title=Daler Mehndi croons for NTR’s Baadshah|publisher=way2movies.com|accessdate=Feb 28, 2013 10:54 AM IST}} However, speculations arised that Simbu replaced Akon for this project later, which were left unanswered.{{cite web|url=http://english.tupaki.com/enews/view/Simbu-replaced-Akon-for-Baadshah/18919|title=Simbu replaced Akon for Baadshah|publisher=tupaki.com|accessdate=Feb 24, 2013 12:03 PM IST}} == Launch == The audio was launched at [[Ramanaidu Studios]] located at [[Nanakramguda]] in [[Hyderabad, India]] through [[Aditya Music]] label on March 17, 2013. [[Dil Raju]], [[S. S. Rajamouli]], [[N. T. Rama Rao Jr.|Jr. NTR]], [[Srinu Vaitla]], [[Bandla Ganesh]], [[Silambarasan|Simbu]], [[S. Thaman]], [[Daler Mehndi]], [[V. V. Vinayak]] and others graced the function.{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/article/91899.html|title=NTR's 'Baadshah' audio launch|publisher=IndiaGlitz|accessdate=March 17, 2013}} [[Kajal Aggarwal]], who was busy shooting for [[All in All Azhagu Raja]] could'nt make it to the audio launch as she missed her Spicejet flight from Coimbatore to Hyderabad. However, she spoke to the media and audience through a video message.{{cite web|url=http://www.123telugu.com/mnews/kajal-aggarwal-to-miss-baadshahs-audio-launch-hm.html|title=Kajal Aggarwal to miss Baadshah’s audio launch?|publisher=123telugu.com|accessdate=March 17, 2013}} The audio launch turned a catastrophic incident as Rajendra Prasad aka Raju, a diehard fan of Jr. NTR died in a stampede unfortunately which made Jr. NTR and the unit to conclude the audio launch then and there fastly. Bandla Ganesh made an announcement that he would be paying 0.5 million rupees as exgratia to Raju's family and Jr. NTR promised to extend his support to the deceased's family.{{cite web|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/junior-ntr-fans-death-at-the-baadshah-audio-launch-shocked-many/379628-71-180.html|title=Junior NTR fan's death at the 'Baadshah' audio launch shocked many|publisher=IBN Live|accessdate=March 18, 2013 06:15 PM IST}} This made the film unit celebrate the success of the audio on March 31, 2013 by a [[Indian Music Industry|Hexa Platinum Disc]] Function held at [[Novotel]] in Hyderabad in a silent and simple manner.{{cite web |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/telugu-flick-baadshahs-platinum-disc-function-will-be-held-today/382284-71-180.html |title='Telugu flick 'Baadshah's platinum disc function will be held today |publisher=[[CNN-IBN]] |accessdate=April 1, 2013 at 02:17 PM IST}} == Track list == {| class="wikitable" |- style="background:#ccc; text-align:center;" |- ! Rama Rao Jr.|Jr. NTR]], [[Kajal Aggarwal]] and many other dancers in Milan, Italy with the theme of [[World Heart Federation|World Heart Day]]. |- | ''Diamond Girl''|| [[Silambarasan|Simbu]], [[Suchitra]] || [[Ramajogayya Sastry]] || 4:04 || Shot on Jr. NTR and Kajal Aggarwal in Spain. Situation is, Hero and Heroine's marriage is on the cards. |} == Reception == The audio got Positive Response from critics as well as audience. ''123telugu'' gave a review stating "Thaman has come up with a very peppy and entertaining music album for ''Baadshah''. ''Baadshah'' is gearing up to be a treat for fans and the music album is no different."{{cite web |url=http://www.123telugu.com/reviews/audio-review-baadshah-peppy-and-entertaining-treat-for-fans.html |title=Audio Review : Baadshah – Peppy and entertaining treat for fans |publisher=123telugu.com |date=March 17, 2013 |accessdate=March 18, 2013}} ''Apherald'' gave a review stating "The entire album sounds like Thaman has patched up all best tunes he composed till date and put up a sweet coated layer of Baadshah on them."{{cite web |url=http://www.apherald.com/Movies/Reviews/16433/Baadshah-Music-Review/ |title=Baadshah Music Review |publisher=apherald.com |date=March 17, 2013 |accessdate=March 18, 2013}} == References == {{Reflist}}

{{db-multiple|A7|G11}} === <big>'''Dice Maniacs' Club, aka The Random Fathom called DMC a Dice Club for Dice Collectors'''</big> === ----
[[Image:dmc8.jpg|thumb|Dice Maniacs' Official Die]]
[https://www.facebook.com/groups/DiceManiacsClub/, The Dice Maniacs' Club aka The Random Fandom], called DMC by many of its members was founded September 14, 1999 by Alexander Simkin, who is also the site manager of this MSN Group.
Pictured is the official DMC dice designed by its members and manufactured by the Polish company [http://q-workshop.com/ Q-Workshop]. And thanks to the DMC managers it is free to its members.
* DMC is an international group with about 300 members from England, United States, Singapore, Portugal, France, Sweden, Italy, The Netherlands, Philippines, Australia, Chile, Germany, Canada, Malta and Switzerland.
* United States from Georgia, Colorado, Alaska, California, New York, Kansas, Pennsylvania, Ohio, Kentucky, Oregon, Florida, New Mexico, Tennessee, Indiana, Washington, Massachusetts, Illinois, Minnesota.
The DMC is a place for everyone and anyone interested in any and all aspects of Dice. We have beginners that start with 7 dice and want to know everything about how to increase their collections to others that have been collecting for decades and have very specific and complex questions. Any and all questions are welcome!
We have a great message board that centralizes these questions and a photo album section, where members can post photos or their dice. We also have links to History of Dice, Mathematics of Dice, and Where to Get Dice. Many members have their own dice websites but if you wish to have your dice online but do not wish to have your own website, Kevin Cook will host your dice for you on his site.
The DMC is the only authority recognized by Guinness to officiate over dice record attempts and has been mentioned in connection with Kevin Cook's record in "The Guinness Book of Records". The DMC was also mentioned in a book about records aimed at younger kids. At one time, the DMC had the greatest number of pictures of dice anywhere on the web. However, that has since changed after Kevin Cook has moved his pictures over to his own site.
*Dr. Alexander Simkin, Site Manager
::Dr. Alexander Simkin, in England, founded The Club after corresponding, trading and meeting dice collectors around the world, especially Dan Glimne in Sweden and Leo van der Heijdt in the Netherlands. He suspected there were many other collectors and alealogists (dice enthusiasts) out there and wanted somewhere for collectors to meet, discuss their collections and post pictures of their dice. MSN Groups offered all those functions, so he went with MSN to form The Club. Alexander got his first set of unusual dice in the early 1980's after getting interested in tabletop role\-playing games, but did not start collecting dice in earnest until 1990. He has about 4,000 dice, but unlike Kevin Cook, cannot be bothered to catalogue them all but has what is probably the most varied collection of dice in the UK. Alexander has been featured in magazines and on national television in the United Kingdom. The only book in English on dice (as opposed to dice games), "Face to Face with Dice", was jointly dedicated to Alexander by the author, Leo van der Heijdt.
*Kevin Cook, Assistant Manager
::Kevin Cook is in the Guinness World Record holding the record for having the world's largest dice collection. At the time of this article he is approaching 24,000 (2008) now over 30,000 (2010) dice. Kevin Cook, lives in Colorado Springs, Colorado, USA, and has been collecting incessantly for 30 years. [http://www.dicecollector.com/ Dice Collector]
*Pwee Keng Ho, Assistant Manager
::Pwee Keng Ho, from Singapore, has traded & will trade with many of the DMC people from all over the world. He is very knowledgeable and shares his knowledge with zest and happily. He also belongs to [http://www.boardgamegeek.com/ Board Game Geek] and like the Alexander & Kevin will make you feel welcome, answer questions, offer advice, and help any way they can to enhance or start you on your way to the joys of collecting dice.
*A few other Notable Members
::We have a member from a Dice Manufacturing Company, Chas, the owner of [http://www.historicgames.com/ MacGregor Historic Games & Pentagram Design].
::And a member that has written a book about dice, [http://home.hccnet.nl/vd.heijdt/ Leo van der Heijdt] 's, "Face to Face with Dice, 500 Years of Dice and Dicing."

In [[Greek mythology]], the '''Elasioi''' ([[Ancient Greek]]: Ἐλάσιοι, meaning 'Averters' or 'Expellers'; in Latin, 'Elasii') were minor personages with power to avert epileptic attacks <ref name="Plutarch">{{Cite book | author = [[Plutarch]] (author); Goodwin, William W. (trans.) | title = Essays & Miscellanies... | date = 1906 | pages = 276 | url =http://books.google.com/books?id=aQtgAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA276&dq=%22Elasii%22+Alexida&hl=en&sa=X&ei=cbt3Up7nEvXesATvoYKwBA&ved=0CEgQ6AEwBA#v=onepage&q=%22Elasii%22%20Alexida&f=false}}</ref>. In the case of someone suffering an epileptic episode in progress, they were sometimes said to cure the ailment by banishing it into the bodies of wild goats<ref name="Owsei Temkin">{{Cite book | author = Owsei Temkin (author) | title = The Falling Sickness: A History of Epilepsy from the Greeks to the Beginnings of Modern Neurology| date = 1945 | pages = 18 | url =http://books.google.com/books?id=P5ktAAAAIAAJ&q=%22Elasioi%22&dq=%22Elasioi%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=N793UoazE6y0sATYmYGgBQ&ved=0CDUQ6AEwAQ}}</ref>.
Yet, their role in society beyond the former remains unclear. Most seem to regard them as divinities of healing; some conflate them with an [[Argos|Argive]] incarnation of [[Castor and Pollux|The Dioskouroi]]<ref name="Plutarch">{{Cite book | author = [[Plutarch]] (author); Halliday, W.R. (trans.) | title = The Greek Questions of Plutarch | date = 1928 | pages = 118 | url =http://books.google.com/books?id=P5ktAAAAIAAJ&q=%22Elasioi%22&dq=%22Elasioi%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=N793UoazE6y0sATYmYGgBQ&ved=0CDUQ6AEwAQ}}</ref> (which implies that there are only two, and that both are male), though other sources claim they are female <ref name="G. Rodney Avant">{{Cite book | author = G. [[File:Mutual Reserve Building 305 Broadway.jpg|thumb|Mutual Reserve Building at 305 Broadway in Manhattan, New York City was built in 1892-94 and was designed by William H. Hume in the Romanesque Revival style in the Richardsonian mode. Designated a New York City landmark on December 20, 2011<ref>NYCLPC Designation Report</ref>]] [[File:621 Sixth Avenue.jpg|thumb|Originally the B. Altman Dry Goods Store, designed by [[David & John Jardine]] and built 1876-77 with addition on the south in 1887 by William H. Hume]] '''William H. Hume''' was an American architect in New York City. His work included the [[Hebrew Orphan Asylum of New York]] (1884) on [[Amsterdam Avenue]] (used as an Army Hall in 1943 and then by [[City College]], the site is now the Jacob H. Schiff Playground),<ref>[http://digital-archives.ccny.cuny.edu/exhibits/lostworld/armyhall.html Army Hall] The Lost World of CCNY: Architectural Gems of Our Past CCNY Libraries</ref> [[Langdon Building]] at 305 Broadway,<ref name=aia>[http://books.google.com/books?id=t0gj61QSgk8C&pg=PA1031&lpg=PA1031&dq=William+H.+Hume+architect&source=bl&ots=Ha-Uqt3F8X&sig=S_2nx8tTGszjS5mt1zg26w9dRww&hl=en&sa=X&ei=acp3UqSfMauhsATUx4CoBA&ved=0CEYQ6AEwBQ AIA Guide to New York City] City College of New York Norval White Professor Emeritus School of Architecture, Elliot Willensky Deceased 1990, City College of New York Fran Leadon Assistant Professor School of Architecture Oxford University Press, May 11, 2010 - Architecture - 1088 pages</ref> [[Scotch Presbyterian Church]] on 96th Church and Central Park West<ref>[From Abyssinian to Zion: A Guide to Manhattan's Houses of Worship] Columbia University Press, Aug 13, 2013 </ref><ref>[http://www.booktown.com/stcroixprints/plan.php?id=2550]</ref> (during the booming 1920s it was replaced by a "Skyscraper Church" designed by [[Rosario Candela]], constructed in 1928-29 it included a 16-story apartment tower and a new church sanctuary and classroom space set into the base and fronting West 96th Street)<ref>[http://www.nycago.org/Organs/NYC/html/SecondPres.html]</ref> [[New Netherland Hotel]] (1892), replaced by the [[Sherry Netherland Hotel]] in 1927,<ref>[http://nyc-architecture.com/UES/UES007.htm]</ref><ref> Stern, Gilmartin and Mellins, Buchman & Kahn </ref> [[Mutual Reserve Building]] at 305 [[Broadway]] and an addition at 615-629 [[Avenue of the Americas]] (Sixth Avenue) between West 18th and 19th Streets in the [[Flatiron District]] of [[Manhattan]], New York City. Originally the [[B. Altman]] Dry Goods Store, built 1876-77 (David & John Jardine), with addition on the south in 1887 by William H. Hume, and on West 18th Street by Buchman & Fox, 1909. B. Altman moved to Fifth Avenue and 34th Street in 1906. The current street retail occupant is The [[Container Store]].
Margot Gayle, writing in ''Cast-Iron Architecture in New York: a Photographic Survey'' (1974), says of 83-87 Grand St., "Architect William H. Hume did it in 1883 as a silk showroom and warehouse - an addition to that section of the building ... which had been erected 10 years earlier. Perhaps it was part of an original grand plan, for the architect had the iron elements for this big addition cast in exactly the same design as for the first building, resulting in a unified whole. The older part of the building carries the date 1872 in its galvanized iron cornice, and displays the foundry label of Lindsay, Graff & Megquier." <ref>[http://www.waltergrutchfield.net/lindsay.htm]</ref> He is also credited with 83-87 Grand St., SW corner of Greene St. (1872) a "serene Tuscan over elaborate Corinithian". <ref>Norval White & Elliott Willensky, AIA Guide to New York City (4th ed., 2002)</ref>
William H. Hume & Son designed the [[Spingler Building]] (1896) at 5-9 Union Square West. It is located on the west side of [[Union Square]] between the [[Lincoln Building (Union Square West, Manhattan)]] and what once was the [[Tiffany’s]] cast iron building headquarters. It was built be William H. Hume & Son who were appointed by the firm of [[James L. Libby & Son]], "who designed it as a commercial building". <ref>[http://www.14to42.net/15street0.4.html]</ref><ref>[http://www.gsapp.org/Archive/HP/2005-2006/resources/resources_primary2.html]</ref> Other work included the Simpson Crawford Simpson Store (1900)<ref name=aia/><ref>[http://books.google.com/books?id=EnM7nPb43DoC&pg=PA110&lpg=PA110&dq=William+H.+Hume+architect&source=bl&ots=oxyXFusKwV&sig=wEy6x1FAEyR0ZRZUagkn3yRX7zE&hl=en&sa=X&ei=xcp3UvnWB4HZsASOwYDwAw&ved=0CDYQ6AEwAzgK#v=onepage&q=William%20H.%20Hume%20architect&f=false] The Architectural Guidebook to New York City Gibbs Smith, 2002 422 pages</ref> and plans for the Masonic Home and School in [[Utica, New York]].<ref>http://books.google.com/books?id=_wwaAQAAMAAJ&pg=PA55&lpg=PA55&dq=William+H.+Hume+architect&source=bl&ots=jHOk2dxDhe&sig=EsK5yLUo5Pky3qv0PBNFXwyNHz8&hl=en&sa=X&ei=xcp3UvnWB4HZsASOwYDwAw&ved=0CC4Q6AEwATgK#v=onepage&q=William%20H.%20Hume%20architect&f=false Architecture and Building, Volume 15 W.T. Comstock</ref><ref>[http://books.google.com/books?id=P3tLAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA146&lpg=PA146&dq=William+H.+Hume+architect&source=bl&ots=Q7jNs36Nu2&sig=YXpSxuUMh0W_K7zOTeKJvcReH-E&hl=en&sa=X&ei=acp3UqSfMauhsATUx4CoBA&ved=0CCsQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=William%20H.%20Hume%20architect&f=false Proceedings of the Grand Lodge of Free and Accepted Masons of the State of New York] Freemasons. [[File:Logo Parque Nacional Submarino La Caleta.jpg|thumb|Logo of La Caleta Underwater National Park]]
The'' 'La Caleta Underwater National Park''' is located approximately 20 kilometers from Santo Domingo, opposite the Las Americas International Airport Dr. Jose Francisco Pena Gomez, La Caleta Underwater National Park is the first underwater park in the Republic Dominican reaches a maximum depth of 180 meters, but has different background levels only reach between 10 and 50 meters, where you can find reefs and fish such as fixtures, or sunfish soldiers who find their coral colonies shelter and food. It is one of the most visited parks in the country submarines both national and international divers. Considered by experts as one of the five best diving in the Caribbean.
In the park there is also a small little beach that is visited in the evenings on weekends for those looking to take a dip in clean water without much competition.
It is classified under the category of ecotourism parks, aimed at the assessment of existing natural resources, encouraging participants in positive behavior towards conservation and respect for nature.
The main tourist attraction is the boat Hickory, sunk in 1984 by the Submarines Research Group (GIS) in order to produce a safe habitat for endangered species. Within the park is the ethnological and archaeological museum, owner of a large collection of objects Tainos. It was created by Decree No. 249 of September 25, 1986.
== Brief history ==
For the arrival of the conquistadors in 1942, '''[[La Caleta, Santo Domingo|La Caleta]]''' was a major Indian settlement. The area currently includes La Caleta, with its surrounding areas, was known as Herds del Toro and, according to tradition, was inhabited by blacks who were engaged in fishing and agriculture.
In 1972, families living around the "little beach" were evicted to start the excavation and construction of the Pantheon Archaeological Museum and the National Park.
== Museum-Pantheon and Archaeological Site ==
In 1972, La Caleta center was established in the scientific community discovered 373 skeletons of pre-Columbian indigenous groups that inhabited the island of Santo Domingo. The finding was of great importance because the remains were associated with three cultural components that inhabited the island: Ostionoid, and Taino Late Late elenoide, the bones date from 650, 750 and 840 years old of our time.
The archaeologists found a secondary burial mound formed by a children's bones that gave the impression of having been tied up like farmers do with the wood . The death of them was due perhaps to an epidemic .
Funeral rites of Aboriginal burials included the fetal position ( flexed ), where the dead were buried with various offerings in accordance with their social ascendancy . Generally, these offerings were composed of marine pebbles , pots , axes and various food debris .
The offerings could appear on the head , on the sides , on the chest , waist or under the corpse. When it came to necklaces, usually located near the neck of the deceased.
The lifting of the site was conducted over two years , the rescue was made ​​by archaeologists Morban Laucer Fernando Luis Chanlatte Baik and Manuel Garcia Arevalo , under the auspices of the Dominican State , besides counting with the participation of researchers from the United States and Puerto Rico .
Since its inception both researchers and the government pondered creating an archaeological museum, with the making of a didactic museology for tourists, students and researchers to the understanding and study of the burial customs of the natives.
In 1974 the Constitutional Government of the late President Dr. Joaquín Balaguer opened Archaeological Museum and La Caleta for tourism , scientific and didactic .

revision.text:
[[File:Michael Ancher Lars Kruse.jpg|thumb|160px|[[Michael Ancher]]: Portrait of Lars Kruse (1908)]]
'''Lars Andersen Kruse''' (1828–1894) was a [[fisherman]] from [[Skagen]] in the far north of [[Jutland]], Denmark. He is remembered not only for his heroic rescues but for his portraits painted by [[Michael Ancher]] and an account of his mistreatment by [[Holger Drachmann]].<ref name=dsd>[http://www.denstoredanske.dk/Dansk_Biografisk_Leksikon/Handel_og_industri/Fisker/Lars_Kruse "Lars Kruse"], ''Dansk Biografisk Leksikon''. {{da icon}} Retrieved 4 November 2013.</ref>
==Biography== From an early age, Kruse took part in many rescues off Skagen's dangerous coasts, helping to save the lives of some 200 people. One of his most heroic exploits was on 27 December 1862 when the Swedish [[brig]] Daphne was stranded of the coast to the north. After the lifeboat had capsized and its crew of eight had drowned, Kruse took his own boat out into the storm and saved the ship's crew. He was immediately assigned to the Life-saving Service where he was put in charge of Skagen's lifeboat. In 1880, he was awarded a silver cross with the inscription: ''Ydmyg i Ordet, stolt i sin Daad, kristen i Gjerning, Mand i sin Baad'' (Humble in speech, Proud in deed, Christly in action, Man in his boat). Kruse drowned in March 1894 off Skagen's north beach, trying to reach land in a violent snowstorm.<ref name=dsd/>
==Kruse in literature and art==
Lars Kruse's courage was recorded by [[Holger Drachmann]] in 1879 when he wrote a poem and descriptive account titled: ''Lars Kruse. En Skildring fra Virkelighedens og Sandets Regioner'' (Lars Kruse. A Picture from Regions of Reality and Truth).<ref>[http://adl.dk/adl_pub/vaerker/cv/e_vaerk/e_vaerk.xsql?ff_id=26&id=3136&hist=L&nnoc=adl_pub "Holger Darachmann: Lars Kruse. En Skildring fra Virkelighedens og Sandets Regioner"], ''Arkiv for Dansk Litteratur''. {{da icon}} Retrieved 4 November 2013.</ref> The tale tells of how initially the authorities refused to award him a medal for his heroic rescues on the grounds that when a poor youngster, he had sold a plank which had drifted up on the beach and kept the money for himself. As a result of Drachmann's critical account of his treatment, he was later awarded a medal.<ref>[http://www.gravsted.dk/person.php?navn=larskruse "Lars Andersen Kruse"], Gravsted.dk. {{da icon}} Retrieved 4 November 2013.</ref>
Lars Kruse appears in several works by [[Michael Ancher]] of the [[Skagen Painters]]: ''Redningsformand Lars Kruse'' (Head of Lifesaving Lars Kruser, 1882),<ref>[http://www.fineart-china.com/htmlimg/image-64597.html "redningsformand lars kruse"], Fineart China. Retrieved 4 November 2013</ref> ''Lystige folk. I købmandens bod'' (Joyful folk in the shopkeeper's bar) from 1883,<ref>[http://www.bruun-rasmussen.dk/item-link.do?iid=715230&lnk=OlderPaintings&mode=detail "709/1245: Michael Ancher: 'Lystige folk'"], Bruun-Rasmussen. {{da icon}} Retrieved 4 November 2013.</ref> and ''Skagensfisker Lars Kruse i eftermiddagslys'' (Skagen Fisherman Lars Kruse in the Afternoon Light, 1908) pictured above.

Located roughly 10 miles south of Boston, the '''Readville Race Track''' had a famous and quite colorful history for both Horse Racing and then Auto Racing.<ref>{{cite book|last=Temple|first=Robert|title=The History of Harness Racing in New England|year=2010|publisher=Xlibris|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=q88nir3IdlwC&dq=Readville+Trotting+Park&source=gbs_navlinks_s}}</ref>
Originally the site of Camp Meigs and home to the 54th and 55th Massachusetts Infantry and the 5th Cavalry training grounds, in 1869 the Norfolk Agricultural Association purchased the land and built a half-mile track. Purchased in 1895 by The New England Trotting Horse Breeders Association, the track was renamed the ''Readville Trotting Park'', expanded to a full mile with the addition of a 3,400 seat grandstand, a clubhouse, restaurant, hotel and stable area. Railroad service was added to accomodate Boston, New York and Connecticut spectators. [http://books.google.com/books?id=q88nir3IdlwC&pg=PA17&lpg=PA17&dq=Readville+Trotting+Park&source=bl&ots=pRHOIhzNpT&sig=MVrBDBGcUULqMf5pBSfrK5aBLFI&hl=en&sa=X&ei=Z8B3UpaMIOL4yQHl8YDQCw&ved=0CEoQ6AEwCA#v=onepage&q=Readville%20Trotting%20Park&f=false]
The public taste for racing shifted with invention of the automobile. In 1903 the first auto race was held at Readville. '''Hermenegildo Seisdedos''', (May 14, 1967), is a Spanish economist and lawyer specialized in [[city marketing]] and [[smart cities]], who manages international forums on urban planning. Ph.D. in Urban Economics, he is a professor at the [[IE Business School]], lecturer and editor in media and international publications. He has published several books, highlighting ''Managing twenty-first century cities'', published in Spanish by [[Prentice Hall]] ([[Financial Times]]).

== Biography == After completing his studies he worked in various companies and started his career as a researcher and consultant for urban management and city marketing.Bachelor in Business Administration by ICADE (Madrid), MBA with specialization in sales and marketing management at IE Business School (IE), and Ph.D. in Economics (Universidad Autónoma de Madrid). http://www.ie.edu/business-school/faculty-research/faculty/ci.gildo-seisdedos.null?_adptlocale=es_ES
In 2007 he concluded his doctoral thesis "Marketing as a strategy tool for the design of urban development “, and began his career as a consultant in different world regions and cities: Madrid,As director of the Forum for Urban Management, he actively collaborated in [[Madrid bid for the 2016 Summer Olympics]] http://www.madrid.es/UnidadWeb/Contenidos/EspecialInformativo/RelacInternac/MadridGlobal/ProyectosEstrategicos/01_ParticipacionEventos/CandidaturaOlimpica/Ficheros/Septiembre.pdfSegovia, Cuenca, Zaragoza, Nuevo Hamburgo (Brasil), Barcelona, Burgos,http://burgosciudad21.org/es/contenido/?iddoc=107 Bogotá, Cuenca (Ecuador), Almería, Irún, Viena and Omán, where he participated in the planning project of the Sultanate.{{cite web|last=Freiland Environmental Consulty|title=Onss Oman National Spacial Strategy|url=http://www.freiland.at/en/menu433/projekte193/|accessdate=25/07/13}}
As a professional in sustainable urbanism and smart cities,http://www.mapfre.com/fundacion/html/revistas/seguridad/nEspecial2009/capitulo2.2.1.htmlpromotes the efficient management of cities that also incorporates technology to citizens.ABC, “Urbanismo Sostenible” by Antonio Villarreal, 13/07/2012 http://www.abc.es/20120713/natural-vivirenverde/abci-urbanismo-201207131001.htmlHe favors innovation and infrastructure services through ICTs, to compete successfully and attract funding, tourism and talent.El País, “Inteligente debe ser el ciudadano, no la ciudad” by Inmaculada de la Vega, 31/05/2012. http://www.dialogosenlagranja.es/Clipping/SmartCities2012/PDFs/El%20Pais-Propiedades_310512.pdf
His book ''Managing XXI century cities'' (2007) published in Spanish, introduced a new methodology, the ''UDS'' or urban development strategy, which included physical planning, strategic town and city brand marketing, and it´s changing the way that cities face the new competitive environment.http://burgosciudad21.org/es/contenido/?iddoc=107
Member of the editorial board of the Journal of Town and City Management www.henrystewart.co.uk and Sustainable City magazine, where he is a regular contributor, participates in international conferences, foros and workshops on the future of the management of cities,He is a regular collaborator at Design Convergence Urbanism [http://www.designconvergence.org/ (DCU)], Member of the International Association of Planners ([[ISOCARP]]) with consultative status at UNESCO and belongs to the Spanish area of the [http://www.unhabitat.org/categories.asp?catid=9 Habitat Committee] (UN Centre for Human Settlements) in search of greater competitiveness, sustainability and social cohesion.http://www.comparteinnovacion.philips.es/ciudades-habitables/una-ciudad-habitable-auna-competitividad-eficiencia-sostenibilidad-medioambiental-y-solidaridad == Publications == * SEISDEDOS, G. Born in 1974, Lionel Guedj studied history and philosophy and is a self-taught filmmaker. He started embarking on a career in music, including work as artistic coordinator for Sony Music/LTC Tristar. In 1999, alongside French photographer Carole Morgane, he created the unique "Les Rendez-vous de la Tour-Eiffel" project that involved taking photographing one celebrity per day over an entire year in front of the Eiffel Tower, leading up to the Millennium Countdown. From Shimon Peres to Johnny Depp, Oliver Stone to Keziah Jones, Boutros Boutros-Ghali to Milla Jovovich, more than 300 celebrities appeared in this photographic record of the period leading to the turn of the millennium. In 2000, Guedj joined the press agency Corbis/Sygma and created their music department, handling Compay Segundo, Angélique Kidjo, U2 and many others. In 2003, Lionel went to West Africa to direct “Mandekalou, Words of Memory”, a film which paid tribute to the tradition of African praise-singing and then joined the team of the unique Silhouette short films festival in Paris. His 2010 film, “Rock’n’roll…Of Corse!” <1> was a film on the amazing life of Henry Padovani, original guitarist of The Police, and featuring Sting, Kim Wilde and The Clash, amongst others, which went on to become part of the Official Selection at the Cannes Film Festival. Lionel is currently working as artistic & executive producer on an international feature “Women Stories” while also developing a feature film “The Drumstick Syndrome" (I'm not a fucking musician, I'm a drummer!").

page.title: Austin E. Cofrin School of Business

revision.comment: Create a page to document the history of the Cofrin School of Business
revision.text:
'''The Austin E. Cofrin School of Business''' is a division of the [[University of Wisconsin-Green Bay]] offering preparation leading to undergraduate degrees in business administration and accounting and a master’s degree in management. The school is named after the entrepreneur who founded the Fort Howard Paper Company in Green Bay and stewarded its growth to become a worldwide brand and one of the world’s largest paper manufacturers. === History === Students have studied business administration and accounting at UW-Green Bay since the school’s inception in the late 1960s. The two programs have always ranked among the University’s most popular academic majors.
It was only relatively recently that a name — the Cofrin name — was attached to the business programs. Dr. David A. Cofrin, shortly before his death in August 2009, announced a $5.5 million gift to the University in memory of his late father, Austin E. Cofrin. It was the largest single private gift for academics in the history of UW-Green Bay. The contribution created a fully endowed chair (an additional faculty position in business), and funded a permanent, universitywide endowment for faculty development and academic enhancements.<ref>{{cite web|title=Austin E. Cofrin School of Business is new at UW-Green Bay|url=http://news.uwgb.edu/log-news/releases/06/30/austin-e-cofrin-school-of-business-1096/|publisher=UW-Green Bay|accessdate=4 November 2013}}</ref>
In recognition not only of that gift but a history of civic involvement and contributions by the larger Cofrin Family, UW-Green Bay Chancellor Thomas Harden announced that, effective July 1, 2010, the name Austin E. Cofrin School of Business would apply to the university’s undergraduate and graduate programs in business and accounting.
“It is a perfect match,” Harden was quoted at the time. “Austin E. Cofrin embodied entrepreneurship in growing his small Green Bay operation into a world leader in the paper products industry. Determination in pursuing innovation and efficiency defined his approach to business. We are proud to honor his memory, and delighted that current and future students in the Austin E. Cofrin School of Business may be inspired by his example.”
Cofrin founded the Fort Howard Paper Co. in 1919 on the west shore of the Fox River. He died in 1980 at the age of 96. Industry colleagues praised Cofrin for his visionary leadership and resourcefulness in solving problems and anticipating trends — Fort Howard was decades ahead of the market in embracing waste paper recycling, for example.<ref>{{cite web|title=A. E. Cofrin biography, 1996 inductees|url=http://www.paperhall.org/inductees/bios/1996/austin_cofrin.php|publisher=Paper Industry International Hall of Fame, Appleton, Wis.|accessdate=4 November 2013}}</ref> === Enrollment === The University’s academic programs in business and accounting date to the school’s founding in the late 1960s and as of fall 2013 account for about 6,400, or roughly one-fifth, of the institution’s 31,000 alumni.
There are more than a thousand current undergraduate or graduate students in the Cofrin School of Business. About 500 undergraduates list Business Administration majors, 150 list accounting majors, and another 350 carry minors in business, accounting or international business. Students choose from degrees or areas of emphasis in accounting, business administration, finance, human resources, management, marketing, and international business. The master’s of management and sustainable management programs currently enroll about three dozen students.<ref>{{cite web|title=Fact Book: Majors and Minors|url=http://www.uwgb.edu/oira/factbook/#Majors_&_Minors_|publisher=UWGB Office of Institutional Research}}</ref> === Faculty === The School lists more than 30 faculty members, making it the largest program at UW-Green Bay. Lucy Arendt, an associate professor of management, is director of the Austin E. Cofrin School of Business and associate dean of the College of Professional Studies. Sue Mattison is UW-Green Bay’s dean of the College of Professional Studies. The senior faculty member in the Cofrin School of Business is Prof. Meir Russ, who teaches courses in management and marketing. He is a consultant to several multinational companies in the areas of global strategic management and knowledge management, and serves as the founding editor of ''The International Journal of Management and Business''. === Accreditation === The University of Wisconsin-Green Bay and its academic programs hold a full 10-year accreditation from the Higher Learning Commission of the North Central Association of Colleges and Schools. The Austin E. Cofrin School of Business is in the process of becoming accredited by the Association to Advance Collegiate Schools of Business. The School of Business has several committees and task forces working to address required elements related to curriculum, assessment and student success. === Mission === In marketing material, UW-Green Bay’s Austin E. Cofrin School of Business says this about itself: “We strive to become the destination school for learners, especially those in the NEW North, who are interested in innovative and problem-focused business programs that prepare them for career success.”<ref>{{cite web|title=Homepage|url=http://www.uwgb.edu/busadmin/|publisher=Austin E. Cofrin School of Business|accessdate=4 November 2013}}</ref> The program states its mission as follows: The Cofrin School of Business offers undergraduate and graduate level programs that:
• Provide a high quality, life-transforming business education that prepares our students to ethically and critically address complex business issues.
• Create knowledge through research to enhance experiential learning and make meaningful contributions to the science of business.
• Partner with businesses to improve sustainability, innovation, and entrepreneurship initiatives by engaging students as informed business professionals.
UW-Green Bay officials note the natural tie between a strong business program at the local public university and prospects for continued economic development. The Green Bay area is famous in business circles for its history of entrepreneurship and innovation, particularly in manufacturing. Along with Fort Howard Paper, other businesses with world-renowned brands include Schreiber Foods in cheesemaking, Green Bay Packaging in cardboard shipping containers and Schneider National in trucking and logistics, among others. Another local business that made it big is the Green Bay Packers professional football team. === Annual Business Week === The College, its students and commitment to the community are showcased each spring during Business Week. The April 2013 edition was typical. A job fair, a panel presentation by alumni offering advice to current students and a variety of career-related workshops were offered. The annual campus-community Business Week dinner featured a keynote by Betsy Michell, vice president of organizational development for the Green Bay Packers.<ref>{{cite web|title=Business Week 2013 summary|url=https://www.uwgb.edu/busadmin/business-week/|publisher=Cofrin School of Business|accessdate=4 November 2013}}</ref> === Prominent alumni === • Mark King, class of 1981, CEO and President, TaylorMade-adidas Golf
• Diane (Dockery) Ford, 1975 Accounting, former VP/Controller, Integrys Energy Group
• Dean Basten, 1989 Accounting, Secretary/Treasurer, Miron Construction
• Jill (Jentink) Lajdziak, 1979, former General Manager, GM’s Saturn division
• Mike Jackson, 1976, former President and COO, Supervalu
• Jeff Cheney, 1979 Accounting, CFO, Kohler Co.
• Jim Wochinske, 1974, Owner and President, Pomp’s Tire Service Inc.
• Rick Chernick, 1974, President and CEO, Camera Corner/Connecting Point
• Rob Cera, 1984, President and CEO, Baylake Corp.
• Greg Santaga, 1984, President and CEO, Green Bay Converting and Hattiesburg Paper
• Bob Pyle, 1983, President and CEO, Pioneer Metal Finishing<ref>{{cite web|title=25 notable alumni|url=http://www.uwgb.edu/25000/featured/|publisher=UW-Green Bay|accessdate=4 November 2013}}</ref> === References === {{Reflist}}

revision.text:
{{db-madeup}} Storm Skoppers - Birds With One Feather
These little birds were first created by Carolyn-Ann-Aish in August, 2013, and are in essence, fictional.
Designed to be a book series for children, the little birds have been crocheted in the style of 'angry birds' that have no wings as such and kind of 'hop' or jump rather than fly.
Because Storm Skoppers perform a kind of 'dance' as they move, which is between skipping and hopping, Carolyn-Ann-Aish, as designer of the toys and books, has created a new word - the noun, 'skopper', and the verbs, skop, skopped, skopping. Because these birds love rain and storms, to be able to do their 'skopping' in puddles, they are called 'Storm Skoppers'.
The first Storm Skopper is named 'Skip' and at the beginning of the series, he believes he is the only one of his kind.

'''José Zúñiga''' (b. 1937) is a [[List of Mexican artists|Mexican painter]] whose work has been exhibited both in Mexico and abroad. His work has been recognized by membership in the [[Salón de la Plástica Mexicana]]. <ref name=miembros>{{cite web |title= Lista de miembros |publisher= Salón de la Plástica Mexicana |url=http://www.salondelaplasticamexicana.bellasartes.gob.mx/index.php/miembrossalon/98-ldm|accessdate= October 18, 2013 }}</ref>
Zúñiga was born in the Carmen Alto neighborhood of the [[Oaxaca, Oaxaca|city of Oaxaca]] in 1937. In 1943, he moved with his family to [[Mexico City]] where he attended middle school, and then studied electronics at a vocational school. However, at age twenty one, he decided to study at the [[Escuela Nacional de Pintura, Escultura y Grabado "La Esmeralda"]] because of his interest in drawing. One of his teachers, [[Benito Messeguer]], urged him to devote himself to painting. Shortly after, he began exhibiting his work in Mexico and abroad.<ref name=bancomer> {{cite book |author=Guillermo Tovar de Teresa |title= Repertory of Artists in Mexico: Plastic and Decorative Arts |volume=III |year=1996 |publisher= Grupo Financiero Bancomer |location=Mexico City |isbn=968 6258 56 6 |page=444}}</ref>
In 1969 he work received two acquisition awards from the national painting competition sponsored by [[CONCANACO]]. In 1970, he won first place in painting at the annual competition of the Salón de la Plástica Mexicana, whose technical council he joined in 1971.<ref name=bancomer/>
From 1972 to 1975 he was in Europe on a grant from the French government to study at the School for Decorative Arts in Paris. While in Europe, he traveled to countries such as Italy, Spain, England, Germany, Greece, Turkey, the former Yugoslavia and the Netherlands. He also created two murals, one at the Rohner studio in 1973 and one called “Homage to [[Pablo Neruda]]” in [[Sardinia]]. He received a second grant to return to Paris from 1980 to 1982 to write a thesis called “La pintura mural Mexicana y sus aportes contemporaneous en otros paises,” related to his interest in urban art.<ref name=bancomer/>
During his career, he has continued to exhibit individually both in Mexico and abroad, as well as teach at La Esmeralda, where he was director from 1991 to 1993. His works can be found in public and private collections such as those of the [[Museo de Arte Moderno]] and the [[Musée National d'Art Moderne]] in Paris.<ref name=bancomer/>
Zúñiga is a [[figurative art|neo figurative painter]], but he considers himself a colorist first. He starts with figurative outlines but there are abstract elements. His work is generally influenced by pre Hispanic colors and lines.<ref name=bancomer/>
